dialogue.speaker: Dilbert
dialogue.text: OH NO... IF THIS GUY TURNS LEFT WHEN I GO RIGHT, WE'LL END UP WALKING DOWN THE HALL RIGHT NEXT TO EACH OTHER.

dialogue.speaker: Dilbert
dialogue.text: I HATE THIS... A HUGE, EMPTY HALLWAY AND HERE WE ARE SYNCHRONIZED LIKE TWO OF THE ROCKETTES.

dialogue.speaker: Unknown
dialogue.text: ... SO THAT'S WHEN I KNOCKED ON THE LADIES' ROOM DOOR, YELLED "JANITOR" AND DUCKED INSIDE.

dialogue.speaker: Dilbert
dialogue.text: AT LEAST YOU MAINTAINED YOUR DIGNITY.
